{
  "texts": [
    "With high computational throughput and extensive framework support, GPUs perform admirably in tasks that require massive parallel computations.",
    "However, power consumption may pose challenges for certain applications, and GPUs have inherent limitations with latency-sensitive processing.",
    "As: FPGAs offer unparalleled flexibility and programmability, enabling users to customize hardware accelerators for specific AI tasks.",
    "Their parallel processing capabilities make them well-suited for real-time processing applications.",
    "However, their programming and optimization may require specialized expertise, and they have lower throughput than GPUs."
  ]
}